 	Ignore a missing or incomplete arch field in the build script. Pakku
 	will pass '\--ignorearch' option to linkman:makepkg[8].
 
+*MinAurAgeHours =* hours::
+	Skip AUR packages (including dependencies and makedepends) whose most
+	recent AUR upload (LastModified) is newer than the given number of
+	hours. Helps avoid pulling in just-uploaded, potentially malicious or
+	broken package updates. The default is 24. Set to 0 to disable. When
+	an explicit target is younger than the threshold, pakku will prompt
+	for confirmation; dependencies, makedepends, and upgrade candidates
+	are skipped with a warning. The check can be bypassed for a single
+	sync invocation with '\--no-min-aur-age'.
+
 *PrintAurNotFound*::
 	Print warnings during upgrade operation when foreign packages were not
 	found in AUR.
@@ -47,6 +57,11 @@
 	Print warnings during upgrade operation when local packages are newer
 	than those found in remote repositories.
 
+*PrintMinAurAgeSkipped*::
+	Print a warning during sysupgrade for each AUR package whose upgrade
+	is being skipped because the new version was uploaded less than
+	+MinAurAgeHours+ hours ago.
+
 *SudoExec*::
 	Automatically exec the program from root via sudo if it is necessary,
 	allowing you to enter password for sudo only once.
